parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the value, but you must make sure that it is unique among all requests. ClientToken can contain only ASCII characters.

>  If you do not specify this parameter, **ClientToken** is set to the value of **RequestId**. The value of **RequestId** for each API request may be different.

parameters.name: DryRun
parameters.description:
Specifies whether to perform a dry run. Valid values:

*   **true**: performs a dry run. The system checks the required parameters, request syntax, and limits. If the request fails the dry run, an error message is returned. If the request passes the dry run, the `DryRunOperation` error code is returned.
*   **false** (default): performs a dry run and sends the request. If the request passes the dry run, a 2xx HTTP status code is returned and the operation is performed.

parameters.name: MaxEntries
parameters.description: The maximum number of CIDR blocks that you can specify in the prefix list. Default value: 50.

parameters.name: PrefixListDescription
parameters.description:
The description of the prefix list.

The description must be 1 to 256 characters in length and cannot start with `http://` or `https://`.

parameters.name: PrefixListName
parameters.description:
The name of the prefix list.

The name must be 1 to 128 characters in length, and cannot start with `http://` or `https://`.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description:
The ID of the region where you want to create the prefix list.

You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: ResourceGroupId
parameters.description: The ID of the resource group to which the prefix list belongs.
